<!-- DAY 1 -->
<div class="section" id="day1">
  <h2><span class="day-label">Day 1 &mdash; Friday 9 October</span>&ldquo;Arrival on the Couch&rdquo;</h2>

  <div class="photo-grid" style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:6px;margin:15px 0;border-radius:10px;overflow:hidden;">
    <img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="Caf&eacute; Sperl" style="width:100%;height:200px;object-fit:cover;display:block;">
    <img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="Vienna aerial view" style="width:100%;height:200px;object-fit:cover;display:block;">
    <img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="Vienna old town street" style="width:100%;height:200px;object-fit:cover;display:block;">
  </div>

  <div class="timeline">
    <div class="timeline-item"><div class="timeline-time">09:05</div><div class="timeline-desc">Fly OS332, London &rarr; Vienna.</div></div>
    <div class="timeline-item"><div class="timeline-time">~12:00</div><div class="timeline-desc">Arrive Vienna. Taxi or CAT train to the apartment (~30 mins). Drop bags, freshen up.</div></div>
    <div class="timeline-item"><div class="timeline-time">13:30</div><div class="timeline-desc"><strong>Caf&eacute; Sperl</strong> &mdash; one of Vienna&rsquo;s most atmospheric old coffeehouses. Billiard tables, bentwood chairs, faded grandeur. Not a Freud-specific caf&eacute;, but very much the kind of Vienna he inhabited. Order a Melange and a slice of Sperl Torte.</div></div>
    <div class="timeline-item"><div class="timeline-time">15:00</div><div class="timeline-desc">Walk through <strong>Naschmarkt</strong> (optional, en route). Vienna&rsquo;s buzzy open-air market &mdash; good &ldquo;arrival energy&rdquo; stop. Olives, cheese, falafel, wine bars. If we&rsquo;re not in the mood, this is the easiest thing to drop.</div></div>
    <div class="timeline-item"><div class="timeline-time">16:00</div><div class="timeline-desc"><strong>Leopold Museum</strong> in the MuseumsQuartier &mdash; the finest collection of Egon Schiele in the world, plus Klimt, Kokoschka, and the whole Vienna 1900 story. The psychological and cultural backdrop to Freud&rsquo;s world. Allow 1.5&ndash;2 hours. <em>Entry: &euro;15 adults. Open daily except Tues, 10am&ndash;6pm.</em></div></div>
    <div class="timeline-item"><div class="timeline-time">20:00</div><div class="timeline-desc">Dinner at <strong>Plachutta</strong> (Wollzeile) &mdash; Tafelspitz, the signature Viennese boiled beef in broth. Emperor Franz Joseph&rsquo;s favourite dish. A ritual. Book ahead.</div></div>
    <div class="timeline-item"><div class="timeline-time">21:30</div><div class="timeline-desc">Evening stroll through the lit-up <strong>Innere Stadt</strong>. Pass <strong>St Stephen&rsquo;s Cathedral</strong>, wander the <strong>Graben</strong>.</div></div>
  </div>

  <div class="info-box">
    <p><strong>&#9749; Caf&eacute; Sperl</strong> &mdash; <em>The Freud connection:</em> Sperl (founded 1880) isn&rsquo;t directly tied to Freud, but it&rsquo;s the best-preserved example of the coffeehouse culture he lived inside. The billiard tables, the newspapers on poles, the unhurried pace &mdash; this is exactly how Viennese intellectuals spent their afternoons in Freud&rsquo;s era. It featured in the film <em>Before Sunrise</em>.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="info-box">
    <p><strong>&#128694; Day 1 walking route:</strong> Caf&eacute; Sperl &rarr; Naschmarkt &rarr; Leopold Museum &rarr; Plachutta &rarr; St Stephen&rsquo;s. Total: ~2.5 km.</p>
    <p><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Caf%C3%A9+Sperl,+Gumpendorfer+Str.+11,+1060+Wien/Naschmarkt,+Wien/Leopold+Museum,+Museumsplatz+1,+1070+Wien/Plachutta+Wollzeile,+Wollzeile+38,+1010+Wien/St.+Stephen's+Cathedral,+Stephansplatz+3,+1010+Wien/@48.2041,16.3665,15z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m32!4m31!1m5!1m1!1s0x476d078504391389:0x1f6a150bbbe7d59c!2m2!1d16.3611!2d48.1998!1m5!1m1!1s0x476d07841e925fff:0x9f6cfba8405482be!2m2!1d16.3636!2d48.1986!1m5!1m1!1s0x476d079018154303:0x212bdcab259a623a!2m2!1d16.3591!2d48.2027!1m5!1m1!1s0x476d0765a9a16af1:0xbb52024a31431ded!2m2!1d16.3787!2d48.2075!1m5!1m1!1s0x476d079f223fce9f:0x17975739fafcdc59!2m2!1d16.3735!2d48.2084!3e2" target="_blank" style="color:#c4a97d;">&#128205; Open walking route in Google Maps</a></p>
  </div>
