<!-- DAY 3 -->
<div class="section" id="day3">
  <h2><span class="day-label">Day 3 &mdash; Sunday 11 October</span>&ldquo;Imperial &amp; Indulgent&rdquo;</h2>
  
  <div class="photo-grid" style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:6px;margin:15px 0;border-radius:10px;overflow:hidden;">
    <img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="Sch&ouml;nbrunn Palace" style="width:100%;height:200px;object-fit:cover;display:block;">
    <img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="Heuriger wine tavern Grinzing" style="width:100%;height:200px;object-fit:cover;display:block;">
    <img src="data:image/png;base64," alt="Caf&eacute; Korb" style="width:100%;height:200px;object-fit:cover;display:block;">
  </div>


  <div class="info-box">
    <p><strong>&#9749; Caf&eacute; Central (Day 3 option)</strong> &mdash; If we didn&rsquo;t linger long enough on Day 2, this is our chance for the full grand-caf&eacute; experience &mdash; the chandeliers, the cake trolley, the piano player, the old Vienna feeling. Worth a proper sit-down.</p>
  </div>

  <p class="muted small">The outliers &mdash; Sch&ouml;nbrunn Palace in the morning, a Heuriger wine tavern in the evening.</p>

  <div class="timeline">
    <div class="timeline-item"><div class="timeline-time">11:00</div><div class="timeline-desc">Leisurely brunch at the apartment or a bakery nearby.</div></div>
    <div class="timeline-item"><div class="timeline-time">12:00</div><div class="timeline-desc">U4 metro to <strong>Sch&ouml;nbrunn Palace</strong> (~15 mins from the apartment). The Habsburgs&rsquo; summer residence. Grand tour of the State Rooms (~1 hour), then wander the gardens and climb up to the Gloriette for the panoramic view across Vienna. Allow 2&ndash;2.5 hours total. Book tickets online in advance. <em>Entry: Grand Tour &euro;29 adults. Open daily 8:30am&ndash;5:30pm.</em></div></div>
    <div class="timeline-item"><div class="timeline-time">15:00</div><div class="timeline-desc"><strong>Caf&eacute; Central</strong> for a quick drink &mdash; the grand caf&eacute; at its afternoon best. Coffee, maybe a slice of cake, soak up the vaulted ceilings and piano.</div></div>
    <div class="timeline-item"><div class="timeline-time">16:00</div><div class="timeline-desc">Back to the apartment. Freshen up, change for the evening.</div></div>
    <div class="timeline-item"><div class="timeline-time">17:30</div><div class="timeline-desc">Tram 38 from Schottentor to <strong>Grinzing</strong> for a <strong>Heuriger</strong> evening (~25 mins). Wine taverns with rustic courtyards, local wine straight from the barrel, cold buffet platters of cured meats, cheese, spreads. October is <strong>Sturm</strong> season &mdash; the partially fermented new wine, cloudy and slightly sparkling. This is a quintessentially Viennese evening. Allow the whole night.</div></div>
    <div class="timeline-item"><div class="timeline-time">Late</div><div class="timeline-desc">Taxi back to the apartment, full of wine and Gem&uuml;tlichkeit.</div></div>
  </div>

  <div class="info-box">
    <p><strong>&#128694; Day 3 route:</strong> Sch&ouml;nbrunn (U4, 15 mins) &rarr; Caf&eacute; Central &rarr; Grinzing (Tram 38, 25 mins).</p>
    <p><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Sch%C3%B6nbrunn+Palace,+Sch%C3%B6nbrunner+Schlo%C3%9Fstra%C3%9Fe+47,+1130+Wien/Caf%C3%A9+Central,+Herrengasse+14,+1010+Wien/Grinzing,+1190+Wien/@48.2139,16.3288,13z" target="_blank" style="color:#c4a97d;">&#128205; Open route in Google Maps</a></p>
