<!-- PRACTICAL -->
<div class="section" id="practical">
  <h2>Practical Notes</h2>

  <h4>October Weather</h4>
  <p>Expect 12&ndash;16&deg;C during the day, cooler in the evenings. Rain is possible. Pack layers, a light jacket, comfortable walking shoes (cobblestones everywhere), and something smart for the Opera.</p>

  <h4>Caf&eacute; Culture Tips</h4>
  <p>Viennese caf&eacute;s are for lingering, not rushing. Order a Melange (the Viennese cappuccino), read the papers, watch the world go by. Nobody will hurry you. Tipping: round up or add 5&ndash;10%.</p>

  <h4>Opera Tickets</h4>
  <p>Check the schedule at <strong>wiener-staatsoper.at</strong> for 10 October. Book seats online in advance for the best choice. Standing tickets (&euro;4&ndash;15) go on sale 80 minutes before curtain &mdash; queue at the Stehplatz entrance on Operngasse.</p>

  <h4>Restaurant Bookings</h4>
  <p>Book <strong>Plachutta</strong> in advance &mdash; it&rsquo;s popular and fills up, especially at weekends.</p>

